Description.to:
h3. What

This task covers the implementation of subscribers to the two notification topics (See epic) for remote sync status and the update to the views to identify the sync status of the result.

h3. Why

This will allow users to view the current sync status of a work order result on-device. This will highlight to users if a work order result has encountered an error syncing to the remote data store.

h3. How

h4. Subscribing to the remote topics.

In the [workorder sync service|https://github.com/feedhenry-raincatcher/raincatcher-workorder/blob/master/lib/angular/sync-service.js#L30] subscribers to the topics can be added to update the status for the data set.

{code:java}
/**
   * Subscribing to remote update failed topic for this workorder data set.
   */
  mediator.subscribe("wfm:sync:" + config.datasetId + ":remote:failed", function(failureNotification) {
    //Reading the data set from local storage and need to mark it as failed locally
    var recordId = failureNotification.uid;

    //Creating a sync manager for this data set.
    //It will return the data manager if already created.
    workorderSync.createManager().then(function(workorderSyncManager) {
      workorderSyncManager.read(recordId).then(function(record) {
        //Updating the sync status of the record
        record._syncStatus = record._syncStatus || {};
        record._syncStatus.code = failureNotification.code;
        record._syncStatus.message = failureNotification.message;

        //Updating the record with the error sync status.
        workorderSync.manager.update(record);
      });
    });
  });
{code}

h4. Adding the sync status to the template 

The workorder result sync status should be displayed as part of the work order.

- In the workorder result list, there should be an icon to identify the status of the sync.
- In the workorder result details, the sync status should also be displayed, along with any error messages.

